-- Kenya Suspends 11 Immigration Officials, Daily Nation Newspaper Reports
-- B y   E r i c   O m b o k
-- 2010-11-02T05:00:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-02/kenya-suspends-11-immigration-officials-daily-nation-newspaper-reports.html
Kenya suspended 11 senior immigration
officials for issuing work permits and Kenyan citizenship to
undeserving foreigners, Nairobi-based  Daily Nation  reported.
Immigration Minister Otieno Kajwang was informed of the
decision, the newspaper said.  Foreign Minister Moses Wetangula “stepped aside” Oct. 27 to
allow investigation into allegations of corruption, while Higher
Education Minister William Ruto was suspended by President Mwai
Kibaki on Oct. 19 pending conclusion of a case involving the
sale of land to the state-owned Kenya Pipeline company.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Eric Ombok  in Nairobi at 
 eombok@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 